-- TPG hires Lazard to sell Australian energy retailer Alinta for about $3.5 bln - sources
-- By Byron Kaye
-- Tue Oct 28, 2014 09:56PM EDT
-- None



SYDNEY, Oct 29 (Reuters) - TPG Capital Management LP [TPG.UL] hired investment bank Lazard Group LLC [LAZAR.UL] to sell Australian gas and electricity retailer Alinta Energy in a deal worth about A$4 billion ($3.54 billion), three sources told Reuters on Wednesday.

